  "commentary": "With SPX at 6598.37 sitting between the max negative gamma wall at 6590 (-9426.6M) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+15597.4M), dealers are likely covering short hedges as we've bounced off the 6590 amplifying level where they were forced buyers. The PIN regime combined with massive positive gamma concentration at 6605 (+15597.4M) suggests dealers will aggressively sell any push toward that level, creating strong resistance just 7 points above current spot. Key inflection points are 6590 downside (dealer buying accelerates) and 6605 upside (dealer selling caps rallies), with the recent wall break and GEX surge indicating we're in a volatile transition zone.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6590-6605 with limited upside due to heavy dealer selling pressure above.",
